  <!-- WHY ANNUAL -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Every Wirral Boiler Needs an Annual Service</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Carbon monoxide safety. Warranty protection. Lower bills. Early fault detection. An annual service at £120 protects everything that matters.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-pros">
          <h3 style="text-align:center;">What an Annual Service Protects</h3>
          <ul class="pf-check-list">
            <li>Carbon monoxide safety. A serviced boiler has its flue and combustion checked. CO has no smell and no colour. A faulty heat exchanger or leaking flue seal is invisible without testing. Annual servicing by a Gas Safe engineer is the only reliable detection method</li>
            <li>Manufacturer warranty maintained. Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal and Baxi all require annual servicing by a Gas Safe engineer and an updated Benchmark certificate. Missing one year can void a 10-year warranty entirely — regardless of how new the boiler is</li>
            <li>Lower gas bills. A serviced boiler runs up to 10 to 15% more efficiently. At current gas prices that saving exceeds the service cost within a single heating season</li>
            <li>Early fault detection before the winter breakdown. A worn component identified in October costs far less to address than an emergency call-out in January when the Wirral is at its coldest</li>
            <li>Inhibitor levels maintained. Inhibitor protects the heat exchanger, radiators and pipework. It degrades annually. Every service includes a test and top-up to the correct concentration</li>
            <li>Legal compliance for Wirral landlords. Landlords are legally required under the Gas Safety Regulations 1998 to hold a valid CP12. See <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE landlord gas safety obligations</a></li>
            <li>Annual reminder included. We add you to our reminder list after your first service and contact you when the next one is due. You never miss a year</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHAT IS CHECKED -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Our Gas Safe Engineers Check During a Wirral Boiler Service</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A thorough 10-point HHIC inspection on every visit. Completed in 45 to 60 minutes for combi boilers, 60 to 75 minutes for system boilers.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue gas analysis</strong><p>Combustion gases tested to confirm correct safe burning. Abnormal readings indicate incomplete combustion and potential carbon monoxide risk. Critical for older boilers common in CH41 and CH42.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas pressure and flow rate</strong><p>Gas supply pressure and flow rate confirmed correct. Low pressure causes lockouts and poor performance. Particularly relevant in older Wirral properties on original gas supply pipes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Burner and heat exchanger</strong><p>Burner removed and inspected for debris and damage. Heat exchanger checked for corrosion and cracking. The most important check for older Birkenhead and Wallasey boilers.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue integrity and external terminal</strong><p>Full flue route inspected including external terminal condition. Additional attention given to corrosion and blockage on coastal West Kirby and Hoylake properties.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Safety devices tested</strong><p>Pressure relief valve, overheat thermostat and gas valve all tested for correct operation under fault conditions.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>System pressure checked</strong><p>System pressure checked and topped up if required. A common lockout cause and heating efficiency reducer across the Wirral.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Inhibitor tested and topped up</strong><p>Inhibitor concentration tested and topped up to the correct level. Standard on every service — never skipped regardless of the service price.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Zone valves, pump and controls</strong><p>For system boilers in CH60, CH61 and CH64, zone valves, pump condition, motorised valves and cylinder thermostat checked. These are the components specific to system boiler configurations.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Magnetic filter cleaned</strong><p>If a magnetic filter is fitted, cleaned as standard. A blocked filter reduces flow and strains the pump. Condition noted and replacement advised if needed.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Full function test and Benchmark updated</strong><p>Full heating and hot water cycle run. Benchmark commissioning record updated. Certificate emailed same day. This is the step that protects your manufacturer warranty.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WARRANTY -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Protect Your Wirral Boiler Warranty with an Annual Service</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Missing a single annual service can void your manufacturer warranty entirely. Here is what each brand requires.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Worcester Bosch. Up to 10 years</strong><p><a href="https://www.worcester-bosch.co.uk/support/warranty-and-guarantee" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Worcester Bosch</a> requires annual servicing by a Gas Safe registered engineer and a completed Benchmark certificate. Missing a service voids the warranty regardless of when the boiler was installed.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Vaillant. Up to 10 years</strong><p><a href="https://www.vaillant.co.uk/homeowners/support-and-spares/warranty/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vaillant</a> requires annual servicing and the service recorded in the Benchmark commissioning checklist. Failure to service annually voids the extended warranty.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Ideal Boilers. Up to 10 years</strong><p>Ideal requires annual servicing by a Gas Safe registered engineer. The service record must be retained and available for any warranty claim. We update the Benchmark on every Wirral service visit.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Baxi. Up to 7 years</strong><p>Baxi requires annual servicing. An unserviced boiler that develops a fault as a result of lack of maintenance will not be covered. We update the service record on every visit.</p></div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fef2f2;border:1px solid #fecaca;border-left:4px solid #dc2626;border-radius:10px;padding:1rem 1.25rem;margin-top:2rem;text-align:center;">
        <p style="color:#7f1d1d;font-size:0.88rem;margin:0;font-weight:600;">On the Wirral, a significant number of engineers do not update the Benchmark commissioning record after a service. If your Benchmark has not been updated, your service has not been fully completed and your warranty protection may be compromised. We update it on every visit without exception.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- BRANDS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Boiler Brands We Service Across the Wirral</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Experienced with all major brands across the full range of Wirral properties. We carry common parts and specialist diagnostic tools for every brand.</p>
      <div class="pf-why-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-why-item"><h3>Worcester Bosch</h3><p>The most popular boiler brand on the Wirral. Experienced with the full Greenstar range across all CH postcodes. We carry common wear parts and can carry out minor repairs on the same visit. Benchmark updated on every Worcester Bosch service.</p></div>
